New Age Inventions
Who invented the telephone? The answer we all know, is Alexander Graham Bell. Who invented the cell phone? This answer does not come readily to our minds. 50 also is the case with almost all the latest inventions, be it a computer mouse, digital camera, or laptop.
We get a lot of information about pioneering inventions like the telephone or electric bulb, even in our school text books. But the interesting stories behind the unique inventions of the last fifty years are not so well known, even though these amazing inventions have revolutionised our daily life, and have, in fact, changed our world in many ways.
S0, this issue of Tell Me Why presents a lot of not so well known information about some marvelous modern inventions, and their little known, but brilliant inventors.
